Module Robotinterface
Package robotinterface.motors

Interface Motor

All Known Subinterfaces:
LinearMotor, Servo
All Known Implementing Classes:
LinearMotorComponent, ServoComponent
public interface Motor
Upper interface for all motors. It is used if we want a unique interface to set all values (e.g. servo angle, linear motor length) with a single operation 'setValue'. This is useful, e.g., if the result of inverse kinematics computation gives a set of (motors, values) to be assiged to move the gripper to a certain position.

      void setSpeed​(double motorSpeed, boolean exceptionIfLimitsExceeded)
      Set the motor speed. This is only supported, if this motor supports flexible motor speeds.
      Parameters:
      motorSpeed - speed
      exceptionIfLimitsExceeded - if true an exception is thrown if the speed limits are exceeded; if false, the speed is always mapped to the valid range
